{
  "comment_text": {
    "sn1.25:1.1": "<i lang='pi' translate='no'>Katāvī</i> (“proficient”) is also found at <a href='https://suttacentral.net/mn82/en/sujato#38.5'>MN 82:38.5</a>. ",
    "sn1.25:1.3": "",
    "sn1.25:1.4": "The questioner wonders how those who have abandoned the conceit of self could use the word “I”. ",
    "sn1.25:2.6": "An “expression” (<i lang='pi' translate='no'>vohāra</i>) is a “conveyance” for sharing meaning. It does not implicate the user in a metaphysical view of “Self”. See <a href='https://suttacentral.net/dn9/en/sujato#53.5'>DN 9:53.5</a>. "
  },
