  "root_text": {
    "sn1.25:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 1.25 ",
    "sn1.25:0.2": "3. Sattivagga ",
    "sn1.25:0.3": "Arahantasutta ",
    "sn1.25:1.1": "“Yo hoti bhikkhu arahaṁ katāvī, ",
    "sn1.25:1.2": "Khīṇāsavo antimadehadhārī; ",
    "sn1.25:1.3": "Ahaṁ vadāmītipi so vadeyya, ",
    "sn1.25:1.4": "Mamaṁ vadantītipi so vadeyyā”ti. ",
    "sn1.25:2.1": "“Yo hoti bhikkhu arahaṁ katāvī, ",
    "sn1.25:2.2": "Khīṇāsavo antimadehadhārī; ",
    "sn1.25:2.3": "Ahaṁ vadāmītipi so vadeyya, ",
    "sn1.25:2.4": "Mamaṁ vadantītipi so vadeyya; ",
    "sn1.25:2.5": "Loke samaññaṁ kusalo viditvā, ",
    "sn1.25:2.6": "Vohāramattena so vohareyyā”ti. ",
    "sn1.25:3.1": "“Yo hoti bhikkhu arahaṁ katāvī, ",
    "sn1.25:3.2": "Khīṇāsavo antimadehadhārī; ",
    "sn1.25:3.3": "Mānaṁ nu kho so upagamma bhikkhu, ",
    "sn1.25:3.4": "Ahaṁ vadāmītipi so vadeyya; ",
    "sn1.25:3.5": "Mamaṁ vadantītipi so vadeyyā”ti. ",
    "sn1.25:4.1": "“Pahīnamānassa na santi ganthā, ",
    "sn1.25:4.2": "Vidhūpitā mānaganthassa sabbe; ",
    "sn1.25:4.3": "Sa vītivatto maññataṁ sumedho, ",
    "sn1.25:4.4": "Ahaṁ vadāmītipi so vadeyya. ",
    "sn1.25:5.1": "Mamaṁ vadantītipi so vadeyya, ",
    "sn1.25:5.2": "Loke samaññaṁ kusalo viditvā; ",
    "sn1.25:5.3": "Vohāramattena so vohareyyā”ti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn1.25:0.1": "Linked Discourses 1.25 ",
    "sn1.25:0.2": "3. A Sword ",
    "sn1.25:0.3": "A Perfected One ",
    "sn1.25:1.1": "“When a mendicant is perfected, proficient, ",
    "sn1.25:1.2": "with defilements ended, bearing the final body: ",
    "sn1.25:1.3": "would they say, ‘I speak’, ",
    "sn1.25:1.4": "or even ‘they speak to me’?” ",
    "sn1.25:2.1": "“When a mendicant is perfected, proficient, ",
    "sn1.25:2.2": "with defilements ended, bearing the final body: ",
    "sn1.25:2.3": "they would say, ‘I speak’, ",
    "sn1.25:2.4": "and also ‘they speak to me’. ",
    "sn1.25:2.5": "Skillful, understanding the world’s labels, ",
    "sn1.25:2.6": "they’d use these terms as mere expressions.” ",
    "sn1.25:3.1": "“When a mendicant is perfected, proficient, ",
    "sn1.25:3.2": "with defilements ended, bearing the final body: ",
    "sn1.25:3.3": "is such a mendicant drawing close to conceit ",
    "sn1.25:3.4": "if they’d say, ‘I speak’, ",
    "sn1.25:3.5": "or even ‘they speak to me’?” ",
    "sn1.25:4.1": "“Someone who has given up conceit has no ties, ",
    "sn1.25:4.2": "the ties of conceit are all dissipated. ",
    "sn1.25:4.3": "Though that intelligent person has passed beyond conceiving, ",
    "sn1.25:4.4": "they’d still say, ‘I speak’, ",
    "sn1.25:5.1": "and also ‘they speak to me’. ",
    "sn1.25:5.2": "Skillful, understanding the world’s labels, ",
    "sn1.25:5.3": "they’d use these terms as mere expressions.” "
  },
